README: This task requires participants to make choices either for themselves or for other individuals in the study between a larger amount of money with a smaller probability of receiving reward or a smaller amount of money with a higher probability of receiving reward. Participants were matched with those with similar preferences. Agent refers to decision-making for Self (0) or Other (1). Probability is the probability of receiving the reward as a proportion. Money is the potential reward in USD.
